p: The identification and characterization of the related compounds from DIBEt were performed in two steps. In the first step, PSI-MS was used to identify the major m/z peaks with a full-scan MS, and then characterized using PSI-MS/MS to obtain the MS/MS fragment of the obtained m/z from the first step. Figure 1 corresponds to the total ion chromatogram of DIBEt in PSI-MS in positive-ion mode, revealing 27 secondary metabolites presented with their molecular formula, monoisotopic mass of experimental ions, and calculated ions in positive modes ( Table 1). All compounds identified in DIBEt were classified into nitrogen compounds, phenolic acids, flavonoids, amino acids, triterpenoids, and others.
